          <msContents>
            <summary>Summary of Advaita (non-dualism) Vedānta doctrine, in verse. The work is supposed to have over 100 verses according to the title, but this work ends at verse 88. The work is often attributed to the Advaitan sage Śaṅkarācārya, though possibly written by one of his followers.</summary>
